Chief Minister and Shiv Sena president Uddhav Thackeray on Sunday told his party leaders he would never abandon the ideology of Hindutva.

In a meeting of party legislators and district heads at the Sahyadri guest house in Malabar Hill, Thackeray said he has not changed the colour or agenda of his party. Shiv Sena leaders said Thackeray had convened the meeting to apprise party legislators and functionaries over the partyâ€™s stance over Citizenship Amendment Act (CAA) and National Register of Citizens (NRC).

